<section>
  <title><literal>etymonLanguage</literal></title>
  <para> Represents one of several allowed values for the <literal>language</literal> property of
  <literal>etymon</literal> objects. Note that as etymologies frequently
  refer to languages that are not covered by ISO standards it is necessary to 
  define codes for all languages used in definitions.</para> 
  <para>
    Properties:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>value</literal> (non-empty string)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
          <literal>iso639-1</literal> (non-empty string) the code in the ISO 639-1
          standard if it exists
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
          <literal>iso639-3</literal> (non-empty string) the code in the ISO
          639-3 standard if it exists
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>displayValue</literal> (optional)
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Children:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>mapping</literal> (zero or more) </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</section>
